Where is reflection useful? Give real world exmple in C++?

in C++ you don’t get reflection “for free,” 
so you only build it when it genuinely pays off.

Here are **real-world scenarios where C++ developers actually use reflection-like systems**, with concrete intuition (not just theory).

---

## 1. Serialization (very common)

**Problem:** Convert objects ↔ JSON / file / network

Without reflection:

```cpp
void save(Player& p) {
    file << p.health << p.mana;  // manual, fragile
}
```

With reflection-like system:

```cpp
serialize(p);  // auto walks properties
```

### Where this is used:

* Game save systems
* Config files
* Network messages

Engines like Unreal Engine rely heavily on reflection for this.

